meanings.definition: To be of higher rank or position than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: In the military, the general will outrank the captain.
meanings.sent2: Her experience and expertise outrank his seniority in this situation.
meanings.sent3: The cat tried to outrank the dog in the household hierarchy.
meanings.sent4: His determination to succeed always manages to outrank any obstacles in his way.
meanings.sent5: The bright student's grades consistently outrank those of his classmates.

meanings.definition: To surpass or exceed in rank or importance.
meanings.sent1: The new technology quickly outranks the old methods.
meanings.sent2: Her dedication to her work allows her to outrank her colleagues.
meanings.sent3: The race to the finish line saw the tortoise outrank the hare.
meanings.sent4: The beauty of the sunset can easily outrank any painting.
meanings.sent5: His generosity towards others always manages to outrank any selfish tendencies.
